Luxfer Holdings PLC Key Developments

Luxfer Holdings PLC Declares Interim Dividend, Payable on August 2, 2017
Jul 3 17
Luxfer Holdings PLC announced that its Board of Directors declared an interim dividend of 12.5 cents (before deduction of depositary fees) per American Depositary Share (12.5 cents per ordinary share of £0.50 each (ordinary shares)). The dividend will be payable on August 2, 2017, to shareholders of record at close of business on July 14, 2017.


Luxfer Holdings plc Announces Executive Changes
May 23 17
Luxfer Holdings PLC announced at its Annual General Meeting held on May 23, that Alok Maskara has been appointed to the board of directors. Mr. Maskara will become chief executive officer of the Group mid-year, succeeding Brian Purves, who is retiring after 15 years as CEO. Until recently, Mr. Maskara was president of the Technical Solutions global business segment of Pentair PLC. Maskara worked at Pentair for eight years, serving as president of progressively larger global business units, including Residential Filtration (2008-2011), Water Purification (2011-2012) and Thermal Management (2012-2014).


Luxfer Group Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Year 2017
May 8 17
Luxfer Group reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company's revenue was $103.4 million compared with $108.8 million a year ago. Operating profit was $10.7 million compared with $13.8 million a year ago. The decrease resulted partially from the fall
in trading profit. Net income attributable to equity shareholders were $6.6 million or $0.25 per diluted share compared with $8.7 million or $0.32 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted net income was $7.2 million or $0.27 per diluted share compared with $8.1 million or $0.30 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $15.3 million compared with $16.8 million a year ago. There was a $1.7 million decrease for the Elektron Division, partially offset by a $0.2m increase in the Gas Cylinders Division. Net cash flows from continuing operating activities were $9.6 million compared with $3.0 million a year ago. As on March 31, 2017, the company's net debt was $105.9 million against $101.9 million at March 31, 2016. Trading profit was $10.5 million compared with $11.8 million a year ago. Profit on operations before tax was $8.6 million against $11.6 million a year ago. Purchases of property, plant and equipment was $2.3 million compared to $3.2 million a year ago. Purchases of intangible assets was $0.4 million against $0.2 million a year ago.

For the year 2017, the company remain confident that its previous guidance to achieve at least 10% improvement in annual EBITDA and EPS remains sound.


