					Full Description



Luxfer Holdings PLC, incorporated on December 31, 1998, is a holding company. The Company is a materials technology company specializing in the design, manufacture and supply of materials, components and gas-containment devices for healthcare, environmental, protection and specialty end-markets. The Company operates through two divisions: Elektron and Gas Cylinders. Its areas of expertise include chemical and metallurgical properties of aluminum, magnesium, zirconium, rare earths and carbon composites. As of December 31, 2016, the Company had operated 20 manufacturing plants in the United States, the United Kingdom, Canada, France, the Czech Republic and China. In the fiscal year ended December 31, 2016, it had manufactured and sold approximately 13,600 metric tons of its magnesium products, approximately 2,500 metric tons of its zirconium products (excluding water weight as sold as a solution) and approximately 1.8 million gas cylinders. The Company's customers include both end users of its products and manufacturers that incorporate its products into finished goods.Elektron DivisionThe Company's Elektron Division focuses on specialty materials based primarily on magnesium, zirconium and rare earths. The Company sells its products through two brands, Magnesium Elektron and MEL Chemicals. Under its Magnesium Elektron brand, the Company develops and manufactures corrosion-resistant and heat- and flame-resistant magnesium alloys used in aerospace, automotive, defense and healthcare applications; magnesium powders used in countermeasure flares that protect aircraft from heat-seeking missiles; magnesium, copper, zinc and brass photo-engraving plates used in the graphic arts industry, as well as a range of engraving-related chemicals and equipment, and its products are used for embossing, foiling and die-cutting in printed media, including decorative packaging, labels and greeting cards, and magnesium products for biomedical applications, including powders for the pharmaceutical industry, lightweight alloys used in orthopedic devices and its exclusive, bioresorbable SynerMag alloy for use in body applications, such as a cardiovascular stent. It also develops and manufactures seawater-activated batteries for military applications, including torpedoes and sonar buoys that locate and track submarines; magnesium-based heating pads for self-heating meals used by the military and by emergency relief agencies, as well as range of self-heating meals, beverages and soups used by military and civilian end users; chemical agent detection and decontamination kits; seawater desalinization kits, and soluble magnesium alloys for use in down-well oil and gas applications.Under its MEL Chemicals brand, the Company develops and manufactures specialty zirconium products, including zirconium-based materials used in automotive exhaust catalysts and in industrial catalysts (both process catalysts and pollution control); zirconium oxides used in electronic and industrial ceramics, including circuit boards, fiber optics, oxygen sensors and fuel cells; filters for drinking water purification and wastewater treatment; thermal barrier coatings for aerospace applications; zirconium-based reactive (crosslinking) chemicals used in oilfield production, paper production, steel production, adhesives, antiperspirants, printing inks, paint and a range of other industrial and consumer products, and zirconium materials being developed for use in biomedical applications, including knee and hip replacements, as well as dental crowns and implants. Its Isolux adsorbent products remove arsenic, lead and other heavy metals from water.The Company competes with SKW Stahl-Metallurgie, Daiichi Kigenso Kagaku Kogyo, Solvay, Neo Performance Materials and Tosoh.Gas Cylinders DivisionThe Company's Gas Cylinders Division manufactures and markets specialized products using aluminum, magnesium, carbon composites and steel. The Company sells its products through two brands, Luxfer Gas Cylinders and Superform. Under its Luxfer Gas Cylinders brand, the Company develops and manufactures aluminum and composite cylinders, systems and accessories used for breathing air containment and life support for firefighters and other emergency-responders, as well as miners and other personnel in hazardous environments; containment of medical oxygen and other medical gases used by patients, healthcare facilities and laboratories; compressed natural gas (CNG) containment for alternative fuel (AF) vehicles, as well as CNG transportation and bulk storage; composite fuel tanks for hydrogen fuel-cell-powered vehicles or generators, as well as cylinders for storage and transportation of hydrogen, and containment of specialty gases for electronics and pharmaceutical manufacturing, environmental monitoring and laboratory applications.The Company also develops and manufactures containment of helium for military and industrial applications; inflation of aircraft escape slides and life rafts, as well as other aerospace applications; containment of carbon dioxide (CO2) for fire extinguishers and beverage dispensing; containment of air and specialized breathing blends for scuba diving, and performance racing applications, including fire extinguisher cylinders, containment of nitrous oxide (N20) for engine performance in racecars and boats, as well as nitrogen containment for tire inflation. In addition to the Company's aluminum and composite cylinders, the Company also manufactures spun steel cylinders for petroleum sampling and for containment of oxygen used by pilots and parachutists at high altitudes. Under its Superform brand, the Company designs and manufactures lightweight aluminum, titanium and magnesium panels superformed into complex shapes for aerospace, automotive, rail, architectural and healthcare components and products.The Company competes with Worthington Industries, Catalina Cylinders, Faber, MES, Hexagon Composites, Agility Fuel Solutions, Quantum Fuel Systems, Everest Kanto Cylinder, Beijing Tianhai Industry, KTK, Magna International, EBP, Fontana, Verbom and Boeing.

