U.S. Silica Holdings has a consensus price target of $56.29, suggesting a potential upside of 77.51%. Given U.S. Silica Holdings’  higher probable upside, analysts clearly believe U.S. Silica Holdings is more favorable than Luxfer Holdings PLC.
Dividends
Luxfer Holdings PLC pays an annual dividend of $0.48 per share and has a dividend yield of 3.8%. U.S. Silica Holdings pays an annual dividend of $0.25 per share and has a dividend yield of 0.8%. Luxfer Holdings PLC pays out 64.9% of its earnings in the form of a dividend. U.S. Silica Holdings pays out -59.5% of its earnings in the form of a dividend. Both companies have healthy payout ratios and should be able to cover their dividend payments with earnings for the next several years. 
Insider & Institutional Ownership
84.5% of Luxfer Holdings PLC shares are held by institutional investors. 1.0% of U.S. Silica Holdings shares are held by insiders. Strong institutional ownership is an indication that hedge funds, endowments and large money managers believe a stock is poised for long-term growth.
